<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-14T13:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-14T13:35:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2373½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName type="from">Colonel E. M. House</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-14T18:35:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1916—6:35 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:06 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Thanks for your information concerning the latest phase of the <hi rend="italic">L</hi>[<hi rend="italic">usitania</hi>]
                                settlement.<note n="23" xml:id="d304fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_339">p. 339</ref>.</note> Germany
                            should, and I think will, agree to German Ambassador’s latest proposal.
                            There are so many other issues involved in the controversy concerning
                            armed merchantmen that I sincerely hope you will leave it in abeyance
                            until I return. I cannot emphasize too strongly the importance of
                            this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>